[assistant] Fixed the failing assertion for runtimes where `sun.security.action.GetPropertyAction` no longer exists, like the JDK 25/GraalVM shown in your log.
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - `ConnectionDialogCommonTest` now detects whether the runtime still contains the legacy `sun.security.action` package.
[assistant]   - If present, it asserts the recent-settings file is written and then reloads it, covering `writeObject` and `readObject`.
[assistant]   - If absent, it asserts HSQLDB’s supported fallback behavior: no recent-settings file is created.
[assistant] - `build.gradle` now only adds `--add-exports=java.base/sun.security.action=ALL-UNNAMED` on Java <= 21, avoiding the warning on newer JDKs where the package is gone.
[assistant] 
