[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering build warnings**\n\nI see the user is concerned about warnings with JDK25, but it’s good to note that warnings don’t necessarily indicate failure. I might suggest adding an export for better clarity. Yet, there are also native build warnings on JDK25. It’s worth thinking about configuring tests specifically for Java 21, while keeping conditioning on native build arguments. That balance could be helpful in managing these issues effectively.\n\n**Considering Java dependencies**\n\nIt seems like everything is fine since I'm using Java 8 dependencies. I need to ensure that I'm adding `tasks.withType(JavaCompile).configureEach { options.release = 21 }`. I don't think I need an import for this. The Native Image on JDK 25 can consume Java 21 class files, which is good. But I wonder if forcing the release to 21 will impact tests that are using newer APIs—luckily, there aren't any JDK 25 APIs that might complicate this.\n\n**Checking Gradle configuration**\n\nI need to check the existing build.gradle file, which seems simple enough but requires edits. I’m considering whether the log4j from previous versions is still relevant. Also, can we use the current JavaVersion? I’m thinking of defining some lists for runtime and JVM arguments. Then there’s the thing about Gradle toolchains. I'm unsure if it needs a JDK or if a JRE would work. I’ll need to make sure Gradle can find the Java 21 launcher.\n\n**Editing build.gradle for tests**\n\nI’m considering configuring tasks for Java 21 by checking for the executable path. Using a hardcoded path isn’t very portable, though. I could check the JAVA_HOME_21 environment variable instead, but that conflicts with the wrapper requirements. Maybe using Gradle toolchains is the way to go. There’s a concern about handling legacy properties in native builds and ensuring the CI uses JDK 21. Also, I need to ensure the build.gradle reflects these edits adequately.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06c78662aabf58b5016a118af86e8c81978e28fa2829623d8e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEYsN1ylL-L0k3dfQzLe4NmKLEdnFWdyozKvofu7oSp3FhYJHuU9fBuYrXmHE24a-udBCaO_ejqhgHMsehjTywHTGVdXII5nVUcNqbCtIjRTwcOn-LJsiB58D1Q8LTZR-RlCnl3cc92KDB_DSjrLqBk1UnFtFAvad-QU7EguYupr0tSsj5bARjN4-zCUbT9HsDRMbWrBgobtMNdqenW5onpaJpn8mLYZKtJOnGb6zEuQRKcPR5PdjI45uoMnxrbjzoCtVBJMTU4_nxuYfs61TLv1DRlPeSzH0QO59-s6dcdYt_CgorahUl7PoYPxTIpt4I9wVtBlY_lnMPygrQA0z-op83AeUlQ64vpFYD8P9q9bPmH_iUO2I2MU1b13YWtI1GlPdlr_2N_AomW-Q53RTeYZLX-c9l6RWRHnvZaM3AVEkxp6BGqNdA9AWj_kyJVqthvm53XR-3TiWnormCKD-J9rnPCeesqJIPX0slvn590LdMaHv7CZ_BCIaasgtYEJFfve67VNu382gJInYyIZSmZvdg3x7-52RLctubjg58kv8PSNIZa1zLb096pe17TPhNCT7aLRMYvXzREoVK73qoBmITK5xRApuKc1qkrIPcYiQUhjUWRKYMSdE6CcFdYzePZxQTteAOfN41cSYnGLqm6WZVOyULmfWndfaHTht-WQodGlF8CSvB2lc9wjGWnDh4NYawWk4mrOLcCTSfjXbZ7Cq1bvD1EVlTIL-YVW7lTkGVFdZX9n0Q69Igd-pw5obSY0sVGC9quPBLPldOz4Nzyyvk5hUkuNB653X1uMbD4PeBe2laJ2Nzqf7CWkM0qTBh90i38z80GIrVNog1muPdO5JcwT68f819X6CKC7f-5pighTO2cJYakpAtHNnaqo_tHxJolKlQ6idS48bcdVEkMoB7xnMEYc_35K4ROjZiG10jr-3_kRfnBrfmVLQi9CHP7-2uoM9_DfPFW4AxwHrDfCh1LzO_Ps4y0v2xnnaW3SBZ0pcQNPWzx9BHF2ukwu6SxyCfWJuvymk7RcXWzGB8bNGu__Z97xg_NxH5DeqUcr0SCdaRllxdI97FL5BCfawdC4JEsOxiMpEUmZ91naVCq0fhJyZseMg715Cp8I88o-5RWwKDDs1Vaajf-BqDRKTh0YYZs_Q2cPyJH-a4AFgXmR4574pDk89gtpX21QGAKqk9lGq0dQrb5mlXyEyeWsajfCP8Di8WOVtob9wxTbzvzyC_A8OynVdPLW3QZ06-6wPGo-heoypGoznvK6xdN4s9aWNlFTiz1wg1uqzM3NYRyzzerKmvq9K-uZ01xrDmZy1KK425Hbq5sAfAFEkeOjPpMlO84A0tgBKaRBL0wj24mdvDnF7G-919pcfiB-7Ayip1srvatHThluO7el5SJgwfixDekgdATQSqcf3muWdbjJ7ppK2Icnw_apYQUWw_kFNqZmd0AfgIADJcWN4-b5S9c81rFn3mvAi1I45X5qmyKN8HQUR9e9q-gPK3BrYO2KimZSy0Owvbp7O1Na9Md8zvVuDjREySkqkzAvQ1hxVrhdzpf4ucv2VTD_jtQSlBL3XjnT6zBQ7qFweLh7UJHzLhnBCKACmqwoRJVHDZPaF3FtodQfGeP5APY0CIxJNq0ulWOj21qk2ugyI030PFh_pw3QO9Vp2Yuglqc1SWg0MHusgvZkg8iXUIzXFevv1IUpKFpAYSGj10SGI0I0LXScNFyxu5DxM4JgWLBO9Lfnv03MCs0F6nJSNkGoMD8x3MmHcFtIVaQYb8UQ2zCjnZOzm2ub08es5j-qVpMrgBfEiERQm1sa